{
  "page": "Manfryd Lothston",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\" style=\"font-style: italic;padding-left: 1.6em;margin-bottom: 0.5em;\">It is unknown whether this character and <a href=\"/index.php/Manfred_Lothston\" title=\"Manfred Lothston\">Manfred Lothston</a> were the same person.</div>\n<table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\"><table style=\"width:100%\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:left;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Lothston\" title=\"House Lothston\"><img alt=\"House Lothston.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/b/b3/House_Lothston.svg/50px-House_Lothston.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/b/b3/House_Lothston.svg/75px-House_Lothston.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/b/b3/House_Lothston.svg/100px-House_Lothston.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;padding:0px 7px 5px 7px\">Manfryd Lothston<br /><span style=\"font-size:80%;font-weight:normal\"> o' the Black Hood</span></td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:right;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Lothston\" title=\"House Lothston\"><img alt=\"House Lothston.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/b/b3/House_Lothston.svg/50px-House_Lothston.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/b/b3/House_Lothston.svg/75px-House_Lothston.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/b/b3/House_Lothston.svg/100px-House_Lothston.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td></tr></tbody></table></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\"></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Alias</th><td>\nManfryd o' the Black Hood<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc4.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc4.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Allegiance</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/House_Lothston\" title=\"House Lothston\">House Lothston</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Culture</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Rivermen\" title=\"Rivermen\">Rivermen</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Father</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Lucas_Lothston_(father_of_Manfryd)\" title=\"Lucas Lothston (father of Manfryd)\">Lucas Lothston</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Book</th><td>\n<i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows\" title=\"A Feast for Crows\">A Feast for Crows</a></i> (mentioned)</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Manfryd Lothston</b>, better known as <b>Manfryd o' the Black Hood</b>, was the son of Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Lucas_Lothston_(father_of_Manfryd)\" title=\"Lucas Lothston (father of Manfryd)\">Lucas Lothston</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Harrenhal\" title=\"Harrenhal\">Harrenhal</a>. He is not remembered fondly.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc4.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc4.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_Events\">Recent Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Manfryd_Lothston&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent Events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Feast_for_Crows\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Manfryd_Lothston&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Feast for Crows\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>On the way to <a href=\"/index.php/Duskendale\" title=\"Duskendale\">Duskendale</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Brienne_of_Tarth\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Brienne of Tarth\">Brienne of Tarth</a> meets Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Illifer_the_Penniless\" title=\"Illifer the Penniless\">Illifer the Penniless</a>, who chastises her for using a <a href=\"/index.php/Shield\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Shield\">shield</a> with the <a href=\"/index.php/Arms\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Arms\">arms</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Lothston\" title=\"House Lothston\">House Lothston</a>. Illifer speaks of the shameful deeds of those who wore the Lothston arms, including Lord  <a href=\"/index.php/Lucas_Lothston_(father_of_Manfryd)\" title=\"Lucas Lothston (father of Manfryd)\">Lucas the Pander</a> and his son Manfryd o' the Black Hood.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc4.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc4.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Manfryd_Lothston&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Raffc4.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc4.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc4.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc4.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\">1.2</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows\" title=\"A Feast for Crows\">A Feast for Crows</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows-Chapter_4\" title=\"A Feast for Crows-Chapter 4\">Chapter 4</a>, Brienne I.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260404025117\nCache expiry: 1209600\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.086 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.310 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 543/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 10570/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 6792/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 453/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 13/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 1062/5000000 bytes\nLua time usage: 0.200/7.000 seconds\nLua virtual size: 6.5 MB/50 MB\nLua estimated memory usage: 0 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%  294.985      1 -total\n 86.00%  253.694      1 Template:Infobox_character\n 85.18%  251.256      1 Template:Infobox\n 11.64%   34.337      1 Template:Hatnote\n 11.43%   33.703     12 Template:Infobox_value\n  4.85%   14.317      5 Template:Infobox_label\n  2.80%    8.258      3 Template:Ref\n  1.69%    4.984      3 Template:Ref/core\n  0.87%    2.565      1 Template:References\n  0.44%    1.303      1 Template:Main_other\n-->\n</div>\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key westeros_awoiaftest-mw_:pcache:idhash:4103-0!canonical and timestamp 20260404025117 and revision id 316866\n -->\n",
